  <body>
    <segment id="1">
Suitable for shared apartments</segment>
    <segment id="17" parent="31" relname="reason">

Shared apartments are not a question of age.</segment>
    <segment id="2" parent="30" relname="concession">  

Of course, the likelihood that teens and twenty-somethings will agree to share a place is greater than that oldies will agree to a life with a shared kitchen and shopping service.</segment>
    <segment id="3" parent="30" relname="span"> 

And yet they do it,</segment>
    <segment id="18" parent="3" relname="evidence"> 

as the example of the senior citizens&apos; home in Bornstedter Feld proves.</segment>
    <segment id="4" parent="19" relname="concession">

Although the concerns of the young are similar to those of the old,</segment>
    <segment id="19" parent="29" relname="span"> 

the form of the shared apartment has changed.</segment>
    <segment id="5" parent="27" relname="list">  

Every pensioner has their own apartment with a bathroom and kitchen.</segment>
    <segment id="6" parent="27" relname="list"> 

Nosiness and cliquishness are unwelcome.</segment>
    <segment id="7" parent="27" relname="list">  

Instead, contact and unconditional neighborly assistance are included in the verbally agreed upon &quot;contract&quot;.</segment>
    <segment id="8" parent="28" relname="span">  

This way, one person saves on an expensive handyman and another saves on a trip to the hardware store.</segment>
    <segment id="9" parent="8" relname="result">  

It should pay off for everyone in the end.</segment>
    <segment id="10" parent="27" relname="interpretation"> 

That was the goal.</segment>
    <segment id="11" parent="23" relname="concession">

For now, the concept seems to be working.</segment>
    <segment id="12" parent="23" relname="span"> 

In addition to structural deficiencies, there is also a downside that those who have the least pension and could have many concerns about the future were not allowed to move into the subsidized apartments.</segment>
    <segment id="13" parent="12" relname="cause">  

The city did not play along here.</segment>
    <segment id="14" parent="25" relname="span">  

Nevertheless, the experiment is noteworthy.</segment>
    <segment id="15" parent="20" relname="condition"> 

And if someone no longer likes it,</segment>
    <segment id="20" parent="21" relname="span"> 

they can always move out again.</segment>
    <segment id="16" parent="21" relname="elaboration">  

Just like any other shared housing situation.</segment>
<group id="21" type="span" parent="22" relname="span" />
